@Reasoning:
Verifies a top-level $-prefixed operator field ($set). MongoDB
distinguishes operator keys (start with $) from data keys at the
translator level, so this test ensures the prefix is preserved in HIR.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build `{"$set": {"status": "active"}}`.
translate_mongodb_to_hir with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input `{"$set": {"status": "active"}}` -> non-null HIR with $set
  preserved as an operator key, passed += 1
- Translator strips the "$" prefix -> may still succeed but semantics
  wrong; if it returns 0 -> "Operator field: translation failed"
@End TestCases

